10 "SECTION 4.1. Chapter 707 of the 1963 Session Laws, as amended by S.L.
11 1973-306, 2002-66, 2004-203, and 2006-171, reads as rewritten:
12 "Section 1. The purposes of this Act, among others, are to provide an enabling Statute, in
13 addition to other Statutes which may be available for such purposes, for the merger of the
14 Laurinburg City School Administrative Unit and the Scotland County School Administrative
15 Unit.
16 "Sec. 2. The Laurinburg City Board of Education and the Scotland County Board of
17 Education, by majority vote of the full membership of each of said Boards, may jointly petition
18 the Scotland County Board of Commissioners for a county-wide election on the following
19 subjects:
20 (a) The merger of the Laurinburg City School Administrative Unit and the Scotland
21 County School Administrative Unit and their respective Boards of Education.
22 (b) The construction of a new consolidated high school to be established to serve the
23 students assigned to Gibson High School, Laurel Hill High School, Laurinburg High School, and
24 Wagram High School, and the issuance of bonds pursuant to the County Finance Act, as
25 amended, for construction of said consolidated high school and for other school purposes in an
26 amount to be determined by the Scotland County Board of Commissioners upon the
27 recommendation of the existing City and County Boards of Education.
28 (c) To require the Laurinburg-Scotland County Board of Education to request and the
29 Scotland County Board of Commissioners to appropriate annually from any local sources,
30 including both general and supplemental tax revenues, such funds as will provide, at a minimum,
31 current expense expenditures per student from local funds which shall be no less than the average
