5 "Sec. 3. Upon the receipt of such petition, it shall be the duty of the Scotland County Board
6 of Commissioners to call an election upon the foregoing subjects within sixty (60) days thereafter
7 and fix the date for the same. The provisions of this Act, relating to the merger of the Laurinburg
8 City School Administrative Unit and the Scotland County School Administrative Unit, shall be
9 contingent upon the approval, by a majority of the voters voting in a county-wide election, of all
10 the proposals as set out in subsections (a) through (d) of Section 2 of this Act. The said election
11 shall be conducted in accordance with the applicable provisions of the General Statutes of North
12 Carolina.
13 "Sec. 4.(a) The Scotland County Board of Education shall be comprised of 8 members. Five
14 of the members shall be residents of the Stewartsville Township and 3 of the members shall be
15 residents of any of the remaining 3 townships in Scotland County at large.
16 (b) Beginning with a primary election to be held in 1974, 2 members who shall be
17 residents of the Stewartsville Township and 2 members, who shall be residents of the other 3
18 townships at large shall be elected to membership on the Scotland County Board of Education
19 for initial terms of 4 years to expire in 1978. Beginning with a primary election to be held in
20 1976, 3 members, who shall be residents of the Stewartsville Township, and 1 member, who shall
21 be a resident of any of the other 3 townships, shall be elected to membership on the said board
22 for initial terms of 4 years to expire in 1980. In 1978 when the initial terms of the first 4 members
23 expire and in the regular county-wide biennial election of that year and in each regular
24 county-wide biennial election thereafter, four members shall be elected for terms of four years
25 each.
26 (c) The initial election for the 4 year terms of the 2 Stewartsville Township members and
27 the 2 members at large shall be conducted according to the procedure set forth in subsections
28 (d)(1) and (2) which provide for the regular elections for these seats beginning in 1978 and the
29 initial election for the four-year terms of the other 3 Stewartsville Township members and the
30 other 1 member at large shall be conducted in accordance with the procedures set forth in
31 subsection (d)(3) and (4) which provides for regular elections for these seats on the board
32 beginning in 1980.
33 (d) The procedure for election of members to the Scotland County Board of Education
34 beginning in 1978 and every 2 years thereafter shall be as follows:
35 (1) At a primary election to be held in 1978 and every four years thereafter at the
36 same time as the primary for the nomination of county officers 2 persons who
37 shall reside within the Stewartsville Township and 2 persons who shall reside
38 within any one of the other 3 Scotland County Townships at large shall be
39 elected for terms of 4 years each.
40 (2) (a) The 2 candidates from Stewartsville Township receiving the largest
41 number of votes in the primary election shall be the nominees whose
42 names shall be placed upon the ballot at the general election and the 2
43 candidates at large from the other 3 Scotland County Townships who

