9 "Sec. 5. The following provisions shall apply in the event of merger under the plan provided
10 for in this Act.
11 (a) The Consolidated Board shall be the County Board of Education in and for Scotland
12 County and shall have county-wide jurisdiction over the public school system in Scotland
13 County, including all municipalities located therein. The name of the Consolidated Board shall
14 be: Laurinburg-Scotland County Board of Education.The public school system of Scotland
15 County shall be known as and shall use the style of "Scotland County School System," and the
16 Board of Education shall be known as and shall use the style of "Scotland County Board of
17 Education."
18 (b) Repealed by Section 2 of Chapter 306 of the 1973 Session Laws.
19 (c) For the fiscal year beginning July 1 immediately following merging of the two Boards
20 of Education, if the Consolidated Board is not created in sufficient time to present its
21 supplemental tax budget and its capital outlay, debt service and current expense budgets within
22 the time prescribed by law for said fiscal year, then the members of the Scotland County Board
23 of Education and the members of the Laurinburg City Board of Education, acting jointly and by
24 a majority vote of all members present, shall determine the amount and contents of the
25 supplemental tax budget requested for the fiscal year beginning July 1 of that year, and shall give
26 the Scotland County Board of Commissioners due notice thereof in time to levy such taxes as
27 may be necessary to provide funds for said budget for that year, and the said two Boards of
28 Education, acting in like manner, shall prepare and submit to the said Board of Commissioners
29 the capital outlay, debt service, and current expense budgets for that fiscal year within the time
30 prescribed by law.
31 (d) Each year following the merging of the two Boards of Education, at the same time
32 the other school budgets are filed, the Laurinburg-Scotland County Board of Education shall file
33 a supplemental tax budget which, when added to the regular budget, shall provide, at a minimum,
34 current expense expenditures per student from local funds which are no less than the average
35 current expense expenditures per student from local funds throughout the State as determined by
36 the latest certification of the State Superintendent of Public Instruction. The said Board of
37 Commissioners shall approve the regular and supplemental tax budgets in the minimum amount
38 provided for above and may approve the regular and supplemental tax budgets in larger amounts,
39 and shall then provide the funds therefor from local funds.For fiscal year 2025-2026, the Scotland
40 County Board of Education shall submit to the Scotland County Board of Commissioners, at the
41 same time the other school budgets are filed, a budget request for operational and capital funding
42 in amounts that would provide an appropriate education to all students in Scotland County during
43 that fiscal year. In evaluating the request, the board of commissioners shall consider the

