13 (e) The Laurinburg-Scotland Scotland County Board of Education, as reorganized, shall
14 appoint a treasurer of all the school funds of the Laurinburg-Scotland Scotland County School
15 Administrative Unit. The treasurer so appointed shall continue to fill such position at the
16 discretion of the Board of Education. No person authorized to make the expenditures or draw
17 vouchers therefor, or to approve the same, shall act as treasurer of said funds. The treasurer shall
18 give bond for the faithful performance of his duties in such amount as the Board of Education
19 may prescribe, but, in no event, for less than twenty-five thousand dollars ($25,000.00). Except
20 as herein otherwise expressly provided, the treasurer shall perform duties prescribed by
21 applicable provisions of Chapter 115 of the General Statutes of North Carolina and shall be
22 subject to all of such provisions of said Act. All sums appropriated by said Board of
23 Commissioners for capital outlay, current expense and to supplement the current expense fund
24 from State and county allotments shall be paid over to the Treasurer of the Laurinburg-Scotland
25 Scotland County Board of Education at reasonable periods after the receipt of said funds by the
26 Treasurer of Scotland County; provided, however, that the said Board of Commissioners shall
27 hold and administer the proceeds of school bond sales in accordance with the procedure now
28 being followed in holding and administering the proceeds of such sales.
29 (f) In addition to the election of a chairman in accordance with the provisions of Chapter
30 115 of the General Statutes, the Laurinburg-Scotland Scotland County Board of Education may
31 also select one of its members as vice-chairman who shall preside at all meetings of the Board in
32 the absence of the chairman, and whenever the Board shall have duly authorized the execution
33 of any contract, conveyance, or other instrument, the vice-chairman shall have the same authority
34 as the chairman to execute the same on behalf of the Board. In the event of absence or inability
35 of both the chairman and vice-chairman, the Board by resolution duly adopted and spread upon
36 the minutes of any meeting, may authorize any other member to execute any contract,
37 conveyance or instrument for and on behalf of the Board.
38 (g) The superintendent of schools shall be ex officio secretary of the Board as provided
39 by G. S. 115-36. The Board may elect an assistant secretary to serve at the pleasure of the Board.
40 The assistant secretary may be, but shall not be required to be, a member of the Board. Such
41 assistant secretary may perform the duties of the secretary of the Board when the secretary is
42 absent from any meeting or for any other reason is unable to perform his duties as secretary. The
43 assistant secretary shall have authority to attest all contracts, conveyances, and other instruments

