1 "Sec. 9. Nothing in this Act shall operate to repeal any special school tax now provided for
2 by law for the Laurinburg City School Administrative Unit or the Scotland County School
3 Administrative Unit unless a majority of the votes cast in said election authorizes the subjects in
4 Section 7 (a) (1) through (4) of this Act and until the merger of the units is effected.
5 "Sec. 9.1. For the 2002-2003 fiscal year only, current expense expenditures from local funds
6 for the Scotland County Schools shall be eight million seven hundred thousand dollars
7 ($8,700,000) and said sum shall be appropriated by the Scotland County Board of Commissioners
8 from local funds, including both general and supplemental tax revenues, and not including fines
9 and forfeitures or restricted use sales taxes authorized by Article 40 or 42 of Chapter 105 of the
10 General Statutes.
11 "Sec. 9.2. Beginning with the 2003-2004 fiscal year, the base amount of funding for current
12 expense expenditures from local funds shall include the previous year's level of current expense
13 expenditures (for example, eight million seven hundred thousand dollars ($8,700,000) in
14 2002-2003), multiplied by one plus the average percentage change in local current expense
15 school expenditures for the two most recent available fiscal years for low-wealth counties in
16 North Carolina (all local expenditures shall include local current expense expenditures incurred
17 by charter schools within the appropriate districts), as determined by the Superintendent of Public
18 Instruction or that person's designee. The average percentage change shall be calculated by (i)
19 adding together for each of the two previous fiscal years the total current local expense
20 expenditures for all low-wealth counties, (ii) dividing each of those totals, respectively, by the
21 number of low-wealth counties receiving low-wealth funding in each year to obtain an average
22 low-wealth county local current expense expenditure for each year, and (iii) comparing the two
23 averages. The average percentage change shall equal the percent difference between the averages
24 for the two years. The resulting product shall then be multiplied by a ratio consisting of the
25 Average Daily Membership used to distribute State funding for the succeeding fiscal year as
26 provided by the Department of Public Instruction, divided by the Average Daily Membership
27 used to distribute funding for the current fiscal year, as determined by the Superintendent of
28 Public Instruction, or that person's designee. The resulting product shall be the required level of
29 current expense funding to be appropriated by the Board of Commissioners from any local
30 sources, including both general and supplemental tax revenues, and not including fines and
31 forfeitures or restricted use sales taxes authorized by Article 40 or 42 of Chapter 105 of the
32 General Statutes.
33 "Sec. 9.3. Notwithstanding the provisions of Sections 9.1 and 9.2 of this act, the Scotland
34 County Board of Commissioners and the Scotland County Board of Education may, in
35 extraordinary economic circumstances, jointly set a level of current expense expenditures for a
36 fiscal year. This deviation from Sections 9.1 and 9.2 of this act shall be valid only if approved by
37 resolution of both boards.
38 "Sec. 10. The public school system of Scotland County shall be known as and shall use the
39 style of 'Scotland County School System' and the board of education shall be known as and shall
40 use the style of 'Scotland County Board of Education'.
41 "Sec. 11. This Act shall be in full force and effect from and after its ratification."".

